      "message": "The use case you\u0027re trying to solve is to show the error stashed in android/error-messages.h\n\nI\u0027d go so far as to add another function there --\n\n  bool android_init_check_error();\n\nThis function,\n  * Checks if any error occured (accessing the internal variables that I recommended to be hidden)\n  * Shows the blocking modal dialogue to the user.\n  * returns true if any error occured.\n\n\nThen use of this functionality becomes simple.\n\nSomewhere deep in the init code, if an error occurs, we need to add:\n\n   android_init_set_error(errcode, kConstErrorMsg);\n\n\nAnd in the main function we do error checking by:\n\n  do_deep_init();\n  if (android_init_check_error()) {\n    return -1;  \n  }\n\n... and such.\nwdyt?",
